PREAMBLE

This repository contains recipes, techniques, and accumulated culinary wisdom
("the Software"). Like all great dishes, it is meant to be shared — but with
conditions. Read carefully before consuming.

---

TERMS AND CONDITIONS

1. FORKING
   You are hereby granted the right to fork this repository, both in the GitHub
   sense and the literal sense. Use of actual forks while reading this license
   is encouraged.

2. REDISTRIBUTION
   You may redistribute recipes contained herein, provided that:
   a) You do not claim the dish as your own at dinner parties.
   b) You acknowledge that "I found it online" is acceptable attribution.
   c) Any modifications (e.g., "I added sriracha") must be documented
      as a separate commit with appropriate commit message.

3. MODIFICATIONS
   Pull Requests are welcome. However, the maintainer reserves the right to
   reject any PR that:
   a) Replaces butter with margarine without written justification.
   b) Reduces cooking time "because I was hungry."
   c) Introduces cilantro into a recipe that was previously cilantro-free,
      without a clearly marked opt-in flag.

4. FEEDBACK CLAUSE
   If you cook a dish from this repository and it turns out badly, you are
   required to open an Issue. This is not optional. Suffering in silence
   does not improve the codebase.

5. WARRANTY
   THIS SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS
   OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO WARRANTIES OF TASTINESS,
   NUTRITIONAL FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, OR NON-SPICINESS.
   IN NO EVENT SHALL THE AUTHORS BE LIABLE FOR ANY OVER-SALTED, UNDER-COOKED,
   OR OTHERWISE CURSED MEALS ARISING FROM USE OF THIS REPOSITORY.

6. TERMINATION
   This license terminates immediately if you use a microwave where the recipe
   explicitly calls for a cast iron pan.

